<paragraph id="8628475BFF818532FF13FF60FECBFED4" blockId="38.[136,1452,158,328]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FF13FF60FEE9FF24" bold="true" box="[189,294,158,184]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Notes:—</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFF818532FE6CFF61FD83FF24" author="Luer, C. A." box="[450,588,158,185]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref29681" refString="Luer, C. A. (1992) Icones pleurothallidinarum IX. Systematic of Myoxanthus. Addenda to Platystele, Pleurothallis, subgenus Scopula and Scaphosepalum (Orchidaceae). Monographs in Systematic Botany, Missouri Botanical Garden 44: 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Luer (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, this uncommon species endemic to central 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FBEDFF60FB6FFF24" box="[1091,1184,158,184]" name="Ecuador" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FA23FF61FEE8FF40" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="octomerioides">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FA23FF61FEE8FF40" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. octomerioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, its yellowish flowers are morphologically similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FBEBFF3DFB18FF40" authorityName="Soto Arenas" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="A. Rich. &amp; Galeotti" box="[1093,1239,195,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FBEBFF3DFB18FF40" box="[1093,1239,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. congestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FAA2FF3DFA6AFF40" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1292,1445,194,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulvinatus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FAA2FF3DFA6AFF40" box="[1292,1445,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. pulvinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is recognized by its abaxially slightly pubescent yellowish flowers and petals with the margins above the middle thicker, forming a sulcus at the abaxial surface, a feature shown in the illustration of the 
<typeStatus id="592CF9F9FF818532FB07FEF5FB16FEB9" box="[1193,1241,267,293]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">type</typeStatus>
and the photo here (Fig. 18B).
</paragraph>
